Traffic on the M4 near Zimbali on the KZN North Coast has been severely affected after a motorcycle knocked a pedestrian on Thursday morning. According to Medi Response’s Paul Herbst, paramedics are currently on scene on the M4 near Zimbali, where a motorcycle has collided with a pedestrian. “Upon arrival of advanced life support paramedics, they found that the motorcyclist had sustained serious injuries whilst the pedestrian sustained minor injuries. “Paramedics are working to manage the scene and stabilise patients,” he said. Traffic on the M4 is heavily affected and motorists are urged to use an alternative route.